The paper focuses on image captioning, which is a task in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed model uses attention mechanisms and adversarial training, which are common techniques in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the linguistic analysis of the generated captions, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of word embeddings and similarity metrics, which are also common in information retrieval (cs.IR).
